REQUIREMENTS
------------
	PHP >= 4.1.0	http://www.php.net
	RRDTool		http://people.ee.ethz.ch/~oetiker/webtools/rrdtool
	
	a cron daemon	(everybody got this)
	a web browser	(duh, you kiddin'!)
	
	* Optionally:
	php-rrdtool     http://www.joeym.net
	                  php rrdtool bindings, may improve performance in 
			  graphs creation
	sudo		http://www.courtesan.com/sudo


SUMMARY
-------
	openSSI-webView aims to be a simple and easy-to-use monitoring solution 
   	for openSSI clusters. It allows the cluster administrator to keep an eye
   	on the cluster health, to quick view each node state and load, and to 
   	watch and even migrate users processes all accross the cluster.
    
	openSSI-webView components are: 
	- a set of PHP scripts, the web interface itself,
	- a couple of shell scripts, to retrieve and store data about the cluster,
	- a cronjob, to update data on a 5mn basis,

DOWNLOAD
--------
	You can get the latest version at 
		http://openssi-webview.sourceforge.net

